annot%20take%20back%20Sindhu.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20made%20the%20remark%2C%20the%20auditorium%20rang%20out%20with%20thunderous%20applause%2C%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%20said%20the%20Sindhi%20community%20needs%20to%20tell%20its%20present%20generation%20about%20its%20history%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20community%20suffered%20the%20most%20after%20Partition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20the%20stubbornness%20of%20just%20one%20person%20led%20to%20the%20Partition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Partition%20of%20the%20country%20took%20place%2C%20lakhs%20of%20people%20were%20massacred.%20A%20large%20area%20of%20India%20became%20Pakistan.%20The%20Sindhi%20community%20suffered%20the%20most%20as%20it%20had%20to%20leave%20its%20motherland.%20Even%20today%2C%20we%20have%20to%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20tragedy%20of%20Partition%20in%20the%20form%20of%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20event%20organised%20by%20the%20Sindhi%20Council%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20have%20to%20move%20forward%20on%20the%20path%20of%20the%20welfare%20of%20humanity%2C%20then%20the%20evil%20tendencies%20of%20the%20society%20will%20have%20to%20end.%20Our%20religious%20scriptures%20also%20give%20us%20the%20same%20inspiration.%20Be%20it%20respected%20Jhulelal%20ji%20or%20Lord%20Shri%20Krishna%2C%20everyone%20has%20talked%20about%20protecting%20the%20good%20and%20eliminating%20the%20evil%20for%20human%20welfare%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20there%20is%20a%20country%2C%20there%20is%20a%20religion%20too.%20And%20when%20there%20is%20religion%2C%20there%20is%20a%20society%20in%20which%20we%20all%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20PM%20Modi%2C%20terrorism%20is%20on%20its%20last%20legs%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%20appealed%20to%20people%20to%20take%20the%20pledge%20of%20%26quot%3Bnation%20first%26quot%3B%20to%20prevent%20the%20repeat%20of%20a%20Partition-like%20tragedy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20prepared%20to%20give%20a%20befitting%20reply%20to%20anyone%20who%20plays%20with%20the%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20nation.%20The%20Sindhi%20community%20is%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20Sanatana%20Dharma%20of%20India.%20The%20community%20has%20progressed%20with%20its%20efforts%20even%20in%20tough%20circumstances.%20It%20has%20set%20an%20example%20of%20how%20to%20reach%20the%20top%20from%20zero%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696791060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2F3mmk1ejc_yogi-adityanath-1200-_625x300_25_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-reason-why-india-cannot-take-back-sindh-from-pakistan-yogi-adityanath-4462178%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Uttar%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20on%20Sunday%20said%20if%20Shri%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20can%20be%20taken%20back%20after%20500%20years%2C%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20why%20India%20cannot%20take%20back%20%26quot%3BSindhu%26quot%3B%20-%20the%20Sindh%20province%2C%20now%20in%20Pakistan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-reason-why-india-cannot-take-back-sindh-from-pakistan-yogi-adityanath-4462178%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-reason-why-india-cannot-take-back-sindh-from-pakistan-yogi-adityanath-4462178%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-reason-why-india-cannot-take-back-sindh-from-pakistan-yogi-adityanath-4462178%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Ring%20Of%20Fire'%20Solar%20Eclipse%20To%20Be%20Visible%20On%20October%2014%2C%20Details%20Here%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESkygazers%20are%20in%20for%20the%20most%20exciting%20astronomical%20event%20of%202023%2C%20when%20a%20rare%20celestial%20spectacle%20will%20grace%20the%20skies%20on%20October%2014.%20Come%20Saturday%2C%20a%20partial%20''ring%20of%20fire''%20solar%20eclipse%20will%20be%20visible%20across%20most%20of%20the%20Americas%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202012.%C2%A0On%20this%20day%2C%20the%20moon%20will%20be%20positioned%20in%20front%20of%20the%20sun%2C%20hiding%20much%20of%20it%20but%20leaving%20a%20brilliant%20ring%20or%20annulus%2C%20as%20per%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fweather%2F2023%2F10%2F08%2Fannular-solar-eclipse-map-explained%2F%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVisible%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20many%20countries%20in%20South%20and%20Central%20America%2C%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20the%20Western%20Hemisphere%20can%20experience%20the%20rare%C2%A0%20phenomenon.%20The%20dazzling%20celestial%20event%20will%20allow%20millions%20of%20people%20to%20witness%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20awe%20and%20the%20wonder%20of%20seeing%20a%20beautiful%20ring%20of%20fire%20eclipse%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Peg%20Luce%2C%20acting%20director%20of%20the%20Heliophysics%20Division%20at%20NASA%20headquarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EYour%20friends%20at%20SciJinks%20are%20counting%20down%20the%20days%20to%20the%20next%20annular%20eclipse%20on%20Oct.%2014%2C%202023.%20Let's%20get%20ready%20together%20by%20learning%20what%20an%20annular%20eclipse%20is!%20%F0%9F%A7%B5%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FFuffFuFxVe%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FFuffFuFxVe%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%E2%80%94%20NOAA%20SciJinks%20(%40scijinks)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fscijinks%2Fstatus%2F1706373861233791059%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2025%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20an%20Annual%20Solar%20Eclipse%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20an%20annular%20solar%20eclipse%20occurs%20when%20the%20Moon%20passes%20between%20the%20sun%20and%20Earth%20while%20at%20its%20farthest%20point%20from%20Earth.%20The%20moon%20does%20not%20cover%20the%20sun%20completely%2C%20leaving%20a%20thin%20ring%20of%20sunlight%20or%20a%20%E2%80%9Cring%20of%20fire%E2%80%9D%20effect%20in%20the%20sky.%C2%A0Meanwhile%2C%20total%20solar%20eclipses%20occur%20when%20the%20moon%20is%20close%20enough%20to%20Earth%20that%20it%20appears%20just%20as%20large%20as%20the%20sun%20in%20the%20sky%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%3Cem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencefocus.com%2Fnews%2Fannular-solar-eclipse-2023-guide%5C%22%3EBBC%20Science%20Focus%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20for%20an%20annular%20eclipse%20to%20occur%2C%20the%20Moon%20must%20be%20in%20its%20new%20Moon%20phase%2C%20and%20far%20enough%20away%20from%20Earth%20so%20that%20it%20looks%20small.%20It's%20therefore%20unable%20to%20completely%20block%20out%20the%20Sun's%20central%20disc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20annular%20eclipse%20will%20travel%20from%20the%20coast%20of%20Oregon%20to%20the%20Texas%20Gulf%20Coast%20on%20Oct.%2014.%20Weather%20permitting%2C%20the%20annular%20eclipse%20will%20be%20visible%20in%20Oregon%2C%20Nevada%2C%20Utah%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Texas%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20parts%20of%20California%2C%20Idaho%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20Arizona%2C%20NASA%20said.%20It%20will%20then%20pass%20over%20Mexico%20and%20Central%20America%2C%20followed%20by%20South%20America.%20The%20eclipse%20will%20end%20at%20sunset%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean.%C2%A0The%20average%20duration%20of%20the%20Oct.%2014%20eclipse%20in%20the%20U.S.%20at%20any%20given%20point%20will%20be%20four%20to%20five%20minutes%2C%20according%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-t-l%3D%5C%22%3Ab%7Ce%7Ck%7C%24%7Bu%7D%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greatamericaneclipse.com%2Foctober-14-2023%5C%22%3EGreat%20American%20Eclipse%20website.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3EWill%20the%20Ring%20of%20Fire%20be%20visible%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98ring%20of%20fire'%20solar%20eclipse%20will%20not%20be%20visible%20in%20India.%C2%A0People%20in%20India%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%C2%A0can%20watch%20it%20via%20the%20official%20NASA%20broadcast%20on%20their%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20which%20begins%20streaming%20at%204%3A30%20p.m.%20on%2014%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FLlY79zjud-Q%3Fsi%3Dsas1Tq_ZMHSLwHUH%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrecautions%20during%20an%20Annular%20Eclipse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Sun%20is%20never%20completely%20blocked%20by%20the%20Moon%20during%20an%20annular%20solar%20eclipse.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20never%20safe%20to%20look%20directly%20at%20the%20Sun%20without%20specialized%20eye%20protection%20designed%20for%20solar%20viewing.%20People%20will%20need%20protective%20eclipse%20glasses%20to%20avoid%20permanent%20eye%20damage%20when%20watching%20it.%20As%20per%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.nasa.gov%2Feclipses%2Ffuture-eclipses%2Feclipse-2023%2F%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20eclipse%20glasses%20are%20thousands%20of%20times%20darker%20than%20normal%20ones.%C2%A0The%20glasses%20also%20must%20have%20the%20ISO%20reference%20number%2012312-2.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20not%20advised%20to%20look%20at%20the%20Sun%20through%20a%20camera%2C%20telescope%2C%20binoculars%2C%20or%20any%20other%20optical%20device%2C%20as%20it%20will%20not%20only%20burn%20through%20the%20filter%20but%20also%20injure%20your%20eyes.%C2%A0%C2%A0Another%20way%20to%20view%20the%20eclipse%20is%20by%20using%20a%20pinhole%20projector.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%2