A%20The%20Search%20for%20Buddhism%20in%20Modern%20India%3Cem%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Navayana%20in%20March%202023%2C%20has%20been%20shortlisted%20for%20the%20%2475%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fheres-the-shortlist-for-the-2023-cundill-history-prize%2F%5C%22%3ECundill%20History%20Prize%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20this%20excerpt%2C%20Ober%20tells%20us%20the%20story%20of%20Raja%20Sivaprasad%2C%20a%20pioneering%20author%20of%20history%20textbooks%20for%20schoolchildren%20in%20the%2019th%20century.%20This%20account%20shows%20us%20how%2C%20contrary%20to%20popular%20belief%2C%20the%20modern%20Buddhist%20revival%20in%20India%20was%20not%20just%20a%20result%20of%20colonial%20interest%2C%20but%20also%20led%20by%20local%20intellectuals%20and%20enthusiasts.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201864%2C%20the%20department%20of%20public%20instruction%20in%20Allahabad%20published%20the%20first%20of%20a%20three-volume%20Hindi%20textbook%2C%20%3Cem%3EItihas%20Timir%20Nashak%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20History%20as%20the%20Dispeller%20of%20Darkness.%20Composed%20by%20the%20Indian%20educator%2C%20Raja%20Sivaprasad%20(1823%E2%80%9395)%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20school%20textbooks%20in%20nineteenth-century%20India%2C%20remaining%20part%20of%20the%20standard%20curriculum%20for%20history%20and%20geography%20classes%20from%20the%20fourth%20to%20the%20tenth%20grade%20in%20the%20North-western%20Provinces%2C%20from%201864%20up%20until%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century.%20While%20Sivaprasad%20was%20not%20a%20scholar%20of%20Buddhism%2C%20he%20was%2C%20as%20Ulrike%20Stark%20has%20argued%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Chybrid%20intellectual%E2%80%9D%20who%20mastered%20both%20Indian%20and%20British%20systems%20of%20learning%20and%20then%20used%20those%20skills%20to%20engage%20the%20colonizers%20%E2%80%9Cas%20interlocutor%20and%20cultural%20broker%20%5Brather%5D%20than%20merely%20as%20%E2%80%98native%20informant%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D.%20This%20makes%20his%20vision%20of%20Buddhism%20of%20particular%20interest%20since%20he%20approached%20it%20not%20from%20the%20position%20of%20a%20specialist%20but%20from%20that%20of%20an%20intellectual%20whose%20background%20and%20training%20lay%20within%20the%20wider%20north%20Indian%20current.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorn%20into%20a%20family%20of%20wealthy%20Jain%20merchants%2C%20Sivaprasad%20received%20a%20private%20education%20in%20Persian%20and%20Sanskrit%20before%20enrolling%20in%20Benares%20Sanskrit%20College%2C%20an%20institution%20first%20established%20by%20the%20Company%20administrator%2C%20John%20Duncan%2C%20in%201791.%20Like%20most%20Indian%20elites%2C%20he%20was%20multilingual%2C%20but%20his%20linguistic%20and%20intellectual%20gifts%20were%20exceptional.%20By%20the%20age%20of%20sixteen%2C%20his%20in-depth%20knowledge%20of%20Jain%2C%20Hindu%2C%20and%20Islamic%20works%2C%20alongside%20his%20growing%20mastery%20of%20English%2C%20Bengali%2C%20and%20Arabic%2C%20gained%20him%20a%20position%20as%20the%20ambassador%20(%3Cem%3Evakeel%3C%2Fem%3E)%20to%20the%20maharaja%20of%20Bharatpur%20at%20the%20British%20Rajputana%20Agency.%20Not%20long%20after%2C%20he%20joined%20the%20foreign%20department%20as%20a%20munshi%2C%20later%20rising%20to%20%3Cem%3Emeer%20munshi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chief%20clerk)%20of%20the%20Simla%20Agency%20and%20becoming%20private%20secretary%20to%20H.M.%20Elliot%2C%20the%20well-known%20British%20historian%20and%20civil%20servant.%20The%20manner%20in%20which%20he%20carried%20himself%20and%20rose%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20colonial%20hierarchy%20was%20as%20much%20a%20matter%20of%20contempt%20to%20some%20as%20it%20was%20inspiration%20to%20others%2C%20a%20sentiment%20well%20captured%20in%20the%20theosophist%2C%20Henry%20Olcott%E2%80%99s%2C%20assessment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20267px)%2085vw%2C%20267px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140556%2FRaja-Sivaprasa-Ai%25CC%2581na-i-ta%25CC%2581ri%25CC%2581khnuma%25CC%2581.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22267%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140556%2FRaja-Sivaprasa-Ai%25CC%2581na-i-ta%25CC%2581ri%25CC%2581khnuma%25CC%2581.jpg%20703w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140556%2FRaja-Sivaprasa-Ai%25CC%2581na-i-ta%25CC%2581ri%25CC%2581khnuma%25CC%2581-176x300.jpg%20176w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140556%2FRaja-Sivaprasa-Ai%25CC%2581na-i-ta%25CC%2581ri%25CC%2581khnuma%25CC%2581-600x1024.jpg%20600w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678925%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22456%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20cover%20of%20the%20Urdu%20edition%20of%20Raja%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20called%20Ai%CC%81na-i-ta%CC%81ri%CC%81khnuma%CC%81.%20Photo%3A%20Bodleian%20Library%2C%20Oxford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%5BSivaprasad%20was%5D%20throughout%20life%20a%20supple%20courtier%2C%20who%20curried%20favor%20with%20every%20European%20official%2C%20played%20the%20sycophant%20and%20got%20titles%2C%20estates%2C%20and%20honors%20of%20sorts%2C%20earned%20the%20contempt%20of%20his%20compatriots%20and%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20that%20of%20the%20whites%20to%20whom%20he%20%E2%80%9Cbent%20the%20pregnant%20hinges%20of%20the%20knee%20that%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94well%2C%20that%20he%20might%20get%20what%20he%20coveted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20description%20indicates%2C%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20accomplishments%20were%20many%2C%20and%20in%201856%2C%20he%20became%20the%20first%20non-European%20inspector%20of%20schools%20in%20the%20North-western%20Provinces%E2%80%94a%20position%20he%20held%20until%20his%20retirement%20in%201878.%20Here%2C%20he%20began%20transforming%20the%20way%20the%20wider%20populace%20conceived%20of%20the%20subcontinent%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20and%20Buddhism%20in%20tow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20opening%20pages%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Sivaprasad%20outlines%20his%20reasons%20for%20composing%20the%20textbook.%20First%2C%20he%20found%20the%20existing%20histories%20of%20India%2C%20written%20by%20Lord%20Elphinstone%20and%20other%20British%20writers%2C%20to%20be%20full%20of%20errors%20and%20historical%20fallacies.%20Second%2C%20he%20wished%20%E2%80%9Cto%20prove%20to%20my%20countrymen%20that%2C%20notwithstanding%20their%20very%20strong%20antipathy%20to%20%E2%80%98change%E2%80%99%2C%20they%20have%20changed%2C%20and%20will%20change.%E2%80%9D%20In%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20the%20study%20of%20the%20past%20was%20necessary%20for%20improvement%20and%20to%20understand%20contemporary%20predicaments.%20%E2%80%9COur%20readers%20must%20learn%20what%20history%20means%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cand%20with%20this%20knowledge%20they%20will%20not%20take%20offense%20at%20what%20we%20write%20%E2%80%A6%20no%20sober%20man%20is%20expected%20to%20go%20through%20these%20pages%20and%20again%20believe%20in%20the%20mythology%20of%20the%20Puranas.%E2%80%9D%20A%20firm%20believer%20in%20the%20model%20of%20%E2%80%9Cscientific%20history%E2%80%9D%20invoked%20by%20his%20former%20teachers%20Elliot%20and%20James%20Prinsep%2C%20Sivaprasad%20drove%20a%20harsh%20wedge%20between%20myth%20and%20history.%20The%20stories%20of%20Rama%20and%20Krishna%2C%20of%20Jesus%20as%20the%20Messiah%2C%20and%20Muhammad%20as%20Prophet%E2%80%94these%20may%20all%20be%20believed%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20ought%20never%20to%20mix%20it%20with%20the%20authentic%20%5B%3Cem%3Epramanika%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20events%20of%20history.%E2%80%9D%20To%20determine%20that%20which%20is%20authentic%2C%20students%20were%20instructed%20to%20base%20their%20arguments%20on%20objectivity%20(%3Cem%3Eyatharth%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20strong%20evidence%20(%3Cem%3Eprabal%20praman%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20being%20forever%20warned%20about%20those%20individuals%20that%20claim%20that%20the%20contents%20of%20their%20books%20(%3Cem%3Epothi%3C%2Fem%3E)%20could%20not%20possibly%20be%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHaving%20outlined%20his%20historical%20method%2C%20Sivaprasad%20explains%20that%20the%20first%20step%20in%20determining%20the%20true%20(%3Cem%3Esachcha%3C%2Fem%3E)%20Indian%20past%20is%20to%20realize%20that%20Indians%20could%20no%20longer%20afford%20to%20ignore%20the%20era%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CBuddha%20which%20begins%20from%20Shakyamuni%E2%80%9D.%20Then%2C%20over%20the%20course%20of%20roughly%20fifty%20pages%2C%20or%20one%20half%20of%20volume%20three%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%20proceeds%20to%20outline%20details%20of%20the%20Buddhist%20tradition%20that%20had%20been%20largely%20unexpressed%20in%20this%20part%20of%20India%20for%20the%20past%20several%20centuries.%20Admittedly%2C%20many%20aspects%20of%20his%20outline%20diverge%20from%20what%20today%20might%20be%20considered%20standard%20accounts%20of%20Indic%20Buddhism.%20While%20this%20is%20due%20largely%20to%20the%20inadequacy%20of%20the%20scholarship%20at%20the%20time%2C%20his%20was%20the%20first%20modern%20Hindi%20text%20to%20recount%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20life%20in%20terms%20(semi-)%20faithful%20to%20normative%20Buddhist%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENarrating%20the%20story%20of%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20Sivaprasad%20recalls%20plots%20familiar%20to%20Buddhist%20cultures%20worldwide%3A%20the%20young%20prince%20abandons%20his%20life%20of%20luxury%2C%20practices%20various%20austerities%20before%20realizing%20the%20error%20of%20asceticism%20and%20gains%20enlightenment%20under%20the%20Bodhi%20tree%2C%20where%20he%20remains%20in%20a%20meditative%20state%20for%20forty-nine%20days.%20Although%20he%20does%20not%20always%20specify%20his%20sources%2C%20much%20of%20the%20content%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20drawn%20from%20Pali-language%20suttas%2C%20the%20English%20translations%20of%20which%20he%20likely%20took%20from%20George%20Turnour%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CPali%20Buddhistical%20Annals%2C%E2%80%9D%20published%20in%201837%E2%80%9338.%20Perhaps%20the%20most%20striking%20divergence%20from%20normative%20biographies%20of%20the%20Buddha%20is%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20argument%E2%80%94contained%20in%20a%20long%20footnote%E2%80%94that%20the%20Buddha%20(Shakyamuni)%20and%20Mahavira%2C%20the%20historical%20founder%20of%20Jainism%2C%20were%20actually%20the%20same%20person.%20Of%20Jain%20background%20himself%2C%20Sivaprasad%20anticipated%20criticism%20from%20Jain%20scholars%20but%20he%20was%20adamant%20in%20his%20view%20that%20ancient%20Jains%20and%20Buddhists%20were%20originally%20followers%20of%20a%20single%20figure%20named%20%E2%80%9CBuddh%20Mahavir%E2%80%9D%20and%20only%20later%2C%20just%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%20river%20flowing%20to%20some%20distance%20branches%20off%20into%20two%20streams%20named%20separately%2C%E2%80%9D%20did%20the%20two%20form%20separate%20paths.%20The%20argument%20that%20Mahavira%20and%20the%20Buddha%20were%20identical%20may%20seem%20odd%20today%2C%20but%20according%20to%20John%20Cort%2C%20it%20was%20only%20after%20the%20towering%20German%20Indologist%20and%20scholar%20of%20Jain%20texts%2C%20Hermann%20Jacobi%2C%20published%20the%20%3Cem%3EKalpasutra%3C%2Fem%3Es%20in%201879%2C%20that%20Orientalist%20scholars%20became%20convinced%20of%20their%20differences.%20Despite%20this%20(mis)interpretation%2C%20the%20descriptive%20narrative%20that%20Sivaprasad%20provides%20is%20surprisingly%20faithful%20to%20Pali%20Buddhist%20sources%20and%20contains%20none%20of%20the%20demonizing%20of%20Puranic%20scriptures%20better%20known%20at%20the%20time.%20In%20alignment%20with%20his%20own%20humanistic%20lens%2C%20Sivaprasad%20also%20firmly%20placed%20the%20Buddha%20in%20temporal%20history%2C%20providing%20the%20reader%20with%20precise%20dates%20and%20times%20at%20which%20certain%20events%20occurred%20in%20his%20life.%20Moreover%2C%20while%20the%20cosmological%20element%20of%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20enlightenment%20is%20not%20ignored%2C%20the%20accent%20on%20his%20humanity%20is%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20327px)%2085vw%2C%20327px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140746%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22327%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140746%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover.jpg%20811w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140746%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover-203x300.jpg%20203w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140746%2FDUST-ON-THE-THRONE%25E2%2580%25949788195539291-cover-692x1024.jpg%20692w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678927%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22484%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDouglas%20Ober%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EDust%20on%20the%20Throne%3A%20The%20Search%20for%20Buddhism%20in%20Modern%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ENavayana%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Buddhism%20itself%2C%20he%20declares%20it%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprogressive%20and%20modern%20creed%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3Eunnati%20ka%20naya%20dhang%3C%2Fem%3E)%20that%20%E2%80%9Cprevailed%20throughout%20the%20whole%20of%20Bharatvarsha%20%5BIndia%5D%E2%80%9D%20for%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20years.%20The%20school%20textbook%20explains%20how%20when%20Buddhism%20was%20at%20its%20apex%2C%20people%20from%20across%20the%20globe%20(%3Cem%3Esari%20duniya%3C%2Fem%3E)%20visited%20India%20to%20study%20at%20its%20universities%20(%3Cem%3Evidyalaya%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Rulers%20outlawed%20capital%20punishment%20(%3Cem%3Eqatal%20ki%20saza%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20built%20large%20hospitals%20where%20the%20poor%20and%20sick%20could%20be%20relieved%20of%20their%20suffering.%20He%20tells%20the%20reader%20how%20the%20bones%20of%20two%20of%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20most%20renowned%20disciples%20were%20recently%20discovered%20near%20Bhopal%2C%20the%20princely%20state%20whose%20Muslim%20begums%20would%20decades%20later%20go%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20protect%20the%20famed%20Sanchi%20stupa.%20He%20also%20reports%20that%20large%20Buddhist%20ruins%20had%20been%20found%20near%20the%20Hindu%20holy%20city%20of%20Benares.%20Narrating%20the%20accounts%20of%20the%20medieval%20Chinese%20pilgrims%2C%20Xuanzang%20and%20Fa-Hsien%2C%20Sivaprasad%20explains%20how%20in%20the%20provincial%20city%20of%20Patna%20(ancient%20Pataliputra)%2C%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20birthday%20was%20celebrated%20with%20great%20pomp%3A%20there%20were%20gripping%20plays%20and%20performances%20(%3Cem%3Enatak%20aur%20lila%20ka%20hangama%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20night-time%20illuminations%20(%3Cem%3Erat%20ko%20roshni%20ka%20tamasha%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20and%20four-wheeled%20chariots%20carrying%20statues%20of%20Buddhas%20and%20Bodhisattvas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20reckoning%2C%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20message%20of%20equality%20and%20non-violence%20was%20a%20direct%20challenge%20to%20the%20brahmanical%20elites%20(%3Cem%3Evedon%20ki%20mahima%20langhan%3C%2Fem%3E).%20In%20a%20remarkable%20passage%2C%20he%20even%20frames%20early%20Buddhism%20as%20a%20popular%20protest%20movement%20against%20the%20tyranny%20of%20society%2C%20comparing%20its%20fight%20against%20brahmanical%20caste%20supremacy%20and%20Vedic%20sacrifice%20to%20US%20president%20Abraham%20Lincoln%E2%80%99s%2C%20struggle%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20emancipation%20of%20slaves%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3Eghulami%20se%20nikalne%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20the%20American%20Civil%20War%20(1861%E2%80%9365)%20and%20the%20Russian%20tsar%20(%3Cem%3Ebadshah%3C%2Fem%3E)%20Alexander%20II%E2%80%99s%20freeing%20of%20the%20serfs%20in%201861%20(49).%20Before%20the%20Buddha%20arrived%20on%20the%20scene%2C%20the%20shudras%20or%20lower%20castes%20were%20treated%20as%20no%20better%20than%20cattle%2C%20he%20argues.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20how%20long%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sivaprasad%20asks%20rhetorically%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20a%20wooden%20vessel%20be%20heated%20without%20setting%20it%20aflame%3F%20%E2%80%A6%20%5BI%5Dt%20is%20a%20general%20rule%20that%20an%20institution%20based%20on%20the%20deprivation%20(%3Cem%3Enuqsan%3C%2Fem%3E)%20of%20the%20many%20for%20the%20profit%20(%3Cem%3Ephaida%3C%2Fem%3E)%20of%20a%20few%20has%20not%20long%20to%20last%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%2C%20when%20Shakyamuni%20spoke%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevil%20of%20violence%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3Ehimsa%20ki%20burai%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20proclaimed%20that%20%E2%80%9CAryan%20and%20non-Aryans%2C%20men%20as%20well%20as%20women%2C%20were%20all%20alike%20able%20to%20choose%20their%20own%20religion%20(%3Cem%3Edharma%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20number%20of%20Indians%20who%20took%20to%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20message%20soared.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20autumn%20for%20the%20Sanskrit%20and%20spring%20for%20the%20Prakrit.%20The%20brahmins%20had%20become%20%5Bpale%20like%5D%20morning%20stars%20while%20the%20shudras%20%E2%80%A6%20bloomed%20like%20lotus%20flowers%20before%20the%20sun.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20progressive%20qualities%2C%20Sivaprasad%20explains%20that%20there%20was%20a%20fundamental%20flaw%20in%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20teaching.%20It%20is%20%E2%80%9Cbeyond%20the%20sphere%20of%20ordinary%20reasoning%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20contends%2C%20%E2%80%9Cattainable%20only%20by%20intuition%20and%20deep%20and%20patient%20meditation%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94unrealistic%20skills%20for%20the%20majority%20populace.%20Thus%2C%20by%20the%20time%20of%20Ashoka%2C%20the%20teachings%20of%20the%20Buddha%20had%20weakened%20the%20people%2C%20allowing%20sacrilege%20(%3Cem%3Edharmaghata%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20ostentatiousness%20(%3Cem%3Eayyashi%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20and%20idol%20worship%20(%3Cem%3Emurti%20puja%3C%2Fem%3E)%20to%20take%20root.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20real%20danger%20was%20not%20its%20idealism%2C%20but%20its%20pacifism.%20In%20a%20statement%20that%20anticipates%20the%20later%20writings%20of%20twentieth-century%20Hindu%20nationalists%20like%20V.D.%20Savarkar%20and%20B.S.%20Moonje%2C%20he%20writes%20that%20Buddhist%20non-violence%20so%20%E2%80%9Csoftened%20the%20heart%20to%20the%20detriment%20of%20the%20land%E2%80%9D%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20tame%20spirit%20of%20petty%20traffickers%2C%20banias%2C%20fell%20upon%20the%20kshatriyas%20%5Bruling%20classes%5D%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Band%5D%20the%20cruelty%2C%20hardheartedness%2C%20rapacity%20and%20debauchery%20of%20the%20Muhammadans%20demoralized%20both%20%5Bthe%20merchants%20and%20ruling%20classes%5D.%E2%80%9D%20By%20the%20thirteenth%20century%2C%20Buddhism%20vanished.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20moment%20it%20was%20printed%2C%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%20ruffled%20the%20feathers%20of%20a%20wide%20swathe%20of%20Indian%20society.%20Many%20protested%20against%20its%20anti-Muslim%20bias.%20Others%20were%20uneasy%20with%20his%20image%20of%20an%20ever-fragmented%20Hinduism.%20Educators%20complained%20about%20its%20excessive%20footnoting%20and%20pedantic%20prose.%20But%20despite%20calls%20for%20the%20book%20to%20be%20removed%20from%20state%20curricula%2C%20it%20only%20grew%20in%20popularity.%20In%20its%20first%20three%20years%20of%20use%20(1864%E2%80%9367)%2C%20the%20department%20of%20education%20in%20the%20North-western%20Provinces%20published%20more%20than%20twenty%20thousand%20copies%20of%20the%20text.%20When%20the%20government%20issued%20translations%20into%20Urdu%20(1867)%20and%20in%20%E2%80%9Ca%20rare%20reversal%20of%20colonial%20textual%20hierarchy%E2%80%9D%2C%20even%20English%20(1874)%2C%20the%20number%20of%20copies%20circulating%20in%20classrooms%20across%20the%20subcontinent%20nearly%20tripled%20each%20year.%20By%201870%2C%20more%20than%20eighteen%20thousand%20copies%20were%20being%20printed%20annually.%20This%20number%20nearly%20doubled%20by%201883.%20Buddhism%20may%20not%20have%20found%20its%20place%20among%20north%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20private%20publishing%20houses%2C%20like%20Naval%20Kishore%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CEmpire%20of%20Books%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20it%20had%20found%20a%20grand%20new%20patron%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20educational%20campaigns%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccivilize%20the%20natives%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20widespread%20use%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20government%20schools%20is%20of%20great%20significance%20considering%20the%20radically%20different%20views%20of%20the%20past%20being%20imparted%20in%20customary%20centers%20of%20learning.%20Popular%20Hindu%20works%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3EVishnu%20Purana%3C%2Fem%3E%20demonized%20Buddhists.%20Temple%20art%20and%20chronicles%20depicted%20Buddhists%20as%20dangerous%20to%20society%20and%20degenerate.%20One%20catches%20glimpses%20of%20these%20attitudes%20in%20contemporaneous%20memoirs.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20Rahul%20Sankrityayan%E2%80%99s%20autobiographical%20portrait%20of%20his%20childhood%20education%20in%20the%20village%20schools%20(%3Cem%3Epathshala%3C%2Fem%3E)%20of%20late%201890s%20Azamgarh%20(in%20modern-day%20Uttar%20Pradesh)%2C%20he%20recalls%20a%20fascinating%20moment%20when%20his%20grandfather%20tells%20him%20that%20the%20carved%20Buddha%20images%20at%20Ajanta%20were%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdemons%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3Erakshasa%3C%2Fem%3Es)%20frozen%20into%20stone%20by%20Hindu%20heroes.%20Colonial%20schools%20not%20only%20challenged%20these%20views%20but%20attacked%20their%20very%20epistemological%20foundations.%20This%20was%20a%20pivotal%20change.%20In%20the%20textbooks%2C%20the%20Buddha%20became%20a%20modern%20icon%3A%20a%20veritable%20Abraham%20Lincoln%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20Jesus%20Christ%2C%20the%20latter%20of%20which%20comparison%20Sivaprasad%20could%20not%20resist%20employing%20(in%20an%20ode%20to%20Max%20M%C3%BCller).%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20interpretations%20strengthened%20the%20tendency%20to%20understand%20the%20history%20of%20Buddhists%20and%20the%20Buddha%20as%20part%20of%20the%20existing%20discourse%20on%20world%20religion%2C%20an%20intellectual%20object%20on%20par%20with%20Christianity.%20Like%20all%20%E2%80%9Cworld%20religions%2C%E2%80%9D%20Buddhism%20was%20ancient%2C%20geographically%20widespread%2C%20had%20its%20own%20historical%20founder%2C%20and%20a%20fixed%20%E2%80%9Ccanon%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%9Cclassical%E2%80%9D%20scriptures%20(typically%20associated%20with%20Sanskrit%20or%20Pali).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Sivaprasad%20was%20deeply%20conversant%20with%20Orientalist%20thought%2C%20one%20needs%20to%20be%20careful%20in%20over-interpreting%20its%20influence.%20The%20historian%20Avril%20Powell%20has%20shown%20how%20many%20of%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20inferences%20were%20drawn%20from%20his%20readings%20of%20Persian%20texts%20and%20much%20vaster%20knowledge%20of%20that%20literature.%20Furthermore%2C%20Sivaprasad%20composed%20the%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%20because%20he%20found%20existing%20British%20histories%20of%20India%20inadequate%20(and%20he%20was%20courageous%20enough%20to%20say%20so).%20While%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20reading%20of%20primary%20Buddhist%20sources%20in%20Pali%20seems%20to%20have%20relied%20upon%20English%20translations%2C%20many%20of%20the%20conclusions%20he%20drew%20must%20be%20situated%20within%20a%20larger%20Jain%20and%20brahmanical%20Hindu%20framework.%20His%20assertion%20that%20Buddhist%20non-violence%20and%20laxity%20of%20morals%20led%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20downfall%20was%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20modern%20extension%20of%20an%20entrenched%20Puranic%20argument%20about%20Buddhism%20leading%20to%20social%20disorder%20and%20decay.%20The%20idea%20that%20Buddhist%20monastics%20were%20hypocrites%20and%20hedonists%20dwelling%20in%20luxury%20was%20also%20a%20common%20trope%20in%20satirical%20Sanskrit%20literature%2C%20in%20which%20Sivaprasad%20was%20likely%20well%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20that%20the%20Buddha%20was%20a%20kind%20of%20socio-religious%20reformer%2C%20a%20Lincoln%20and%20Luther%20combined%20into%20one%2C%20was%20certainly%20a%20novel%20proclamation%20that%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20his%20intimate%20knowledge%20of%20Euro-American%20history%20and%20current%20events.%20While%20the%20notion%20that%20the%20Buddha%20was%20a%20reformer%20may%20be%20a%20historical%20anachronism%2C%20it%20has%20maintained%20its%20steam%20to%20the%20present%20day%20because%20Sivaprasad%E2%80%99s%20critique%20of%20Vedic%20norms%20has%20deep%20and%20discursive%20underpinnings%20in%20the%20literary%20traditions%20of%20both%20Buddhists%20and%20brahmins.%20Lastly%2C%20his%20argument%20that%20Buddhists%20once%20formed%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20Indian%20population%2C%20particularly%20among%20oppressed%20castes%2C%20has%20had%20an%20equally%20long%20shelf%20life%2C%20with%20real-life%20repercussions%20among%20colonial%20and%20post-colonial%20dalit%E2%80%93bahujan%20populations.%20Ultimately%2C%20many%20of%20his%20claims%20regarding%20Buddhist%20history%20are%20derived%20from%20both%20pre-modern%20sources%20and%20colonial%20scholarship.%20The%20%3Cem%3EItihas%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20best%20seen%20in%20this%20vein%2C%20as%20a%20hybrid%20intellectual%E2%80%99s%20synthesis%20of%20the%20available%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDouglas%20Ober%20teaches%20history%20at%20Fort%20Lewis%20College%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20is%20an%20honorary%20research%20associate%20in%20the%20Centre%20for%20India%20and%20South%20Asia%20Research%20at%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20edited%20excerpt%20where%20the%20academic%20notes%20and%20references%20have%20been%20removed.%20Excerpted%20with%20permission%20from%20Navayana.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696755638000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08140651%2FOber-collage-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fraja-sivaprasad-and-the-lost-history-of-buddhism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Douglas%20Ober%20tells%20us%20the%20story%20of%20Raja%20Sivaprasad%2C%20a%20pioneeri